frameDefinitions: An Agent causes a Theme to move away from a location, the Source.
These are words relating to emptying containers and clearing areas of some substance or items.
An Inspector directs his/her perceptual attention to a Ground to ascertain whether the Ground is intact or  whether an Unwanted_entity is present.
A Helper benefits a Benefited_party by enabling the culmination of a Goal that the Benefited_party has.
Generally without overall (translational) motion,  an Agent places a Theme at a location, the Goal, which is profiled.
In this frame a Source_emitter discharges its Emission along a Path or to a Goal.  ' (1)
frameExamples: I saw that several men in dark suits had <t>removed</t> all of the evidence from the scene.
The players <t>emptied</t> the bucket over his head.
The police removed Flonnory and Barbour from the automobile and <t>frisked</t> them for weapons.
Will you <t>help</t> the Government find your brother?
David <t>placed</t> his briefcase on the floor.
(1) The factory <t>exudes</t> toxic fumes from three large chimneys.
listRoleDefinitions: The <fen>Agent</fen> is the person (or other force) that causes the <fen>Theme</fen> to move.
Theme is the object that changes location.
The <fen>Source</fen> is the initial location of the <fen>Theme</fen>, before it changes location.
The non-Agentive cause of the removing event.
The time at which the removal takes place.
The location where the removal takes place.
The <fen>Agent</fen> is the entity that does the emptying.
The <fen>Theme</fen>, when overtly expressed, invariably occurs in a PP Complement headed by 'of'.
The <fen>Source</fen> is the region or container which is emptied of something.  In this frame, the <fen>Source</fen> occurs as an NP Object.
The <fen>Cause</fen> is the non-sentient force which instigates the emptying.
The time at which the emptying takes place.
The location where the emptying takes place.
The person who inspects the <fen>Ground</fen> to see if it is intact or without blemish.
The entity that the <fen>Inspector</fen> inspects with his senses to ascertain whether it is intact.
An entity whose presence would impair the acceptability or usefulness of the <fen>Ground</fen>.

Some of the words in this frame occur with a constituent that expresses the desired outcome of the inspection.  Normally this constituent is a PP Complement headed by <ment>for</ment>, or a <ment>to</ment>-marked VP Complement.
The desirable state of affairs which the <fen>Inspector</fen> hopes to find to obtain when inspecting the <fen>Ground</fen>.
The <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Inspector</fen> examines the <fen>Ground</fen>.
The <fen>Benefited_party</fen> receives a benefit from the action of the <fen>Helper</fen>.
The <fen>Helper</fen> performs some action that benefits the <fen>Benefited_party</fen>.
The desirable state of affairs that the <fen>Benefited_party</fen> is involved in and which is enabled by the <fen>Helper</fen>.
This role identifies a <fen>Focal_entity</fen> involved in achieving the <fen>Goal</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the Assistance occurs.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the Assistance occurs.
The <fen>Agent</fen> is the person (or other force) that causes the <fen>Theme</fen> to move.
The <fen>Theme</fen> is the object that changes location during the Placing.
The role <fen>Goal</fen> is the location where the <fen>Theme</fen> ends up. This role is profiled by words in this frame.
<fen>Time</fen> is when the Placing occurs
The <fen>Place</fen> indicates where the Placing occurs.
The <fen>Source_emitter</fen> is the item  from which the <fen>Emission</fen> are discharged.
The <fen>Emission</fen>s are discharged out of the <fen>Source_emitter</fen> .
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when  the <fen>Source_emitter</fen> emits the <fen>Emission</fen>.
